    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "@Haroenv I apologize again for asking in wrong window. Will post the same in react instantsearch repo.\r\n\r\nI have a refinement as below which has defaultRefinement set\r\n```jsx\r\n<RefinementList attribute=\"specialities\" defaultRefinement={['foo', 'bar']} />\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe clearRefinement method as implemented below\r\n```jsx\r\nconst ClearAllRefinements = ({refine, items}) => {\r\n  return  <TouchableHighlight underlayColor=\"#eef0f0\" onPress={() => refine(items)} style={{height: 50, flex: 1, flexDirection: 'column', justifyContent: 'center', alignItems: 'center'}}>\r\n            <Text>Clear</Text>\r\n          </TouchableHighlight>\r\n};\r\n\r\nconst ConnectedClearAllRefinements = connectCurrentRefinements(ClearAllRefinements);\r\n\r\n<ConnectedClearAllRefinements />\r\n```\r\nclears all filters including the defaultRefinements. I don't want that defaultRefinement to be cleared off.\r\n\r\nIs there any option parameter which I can pass to `<ConnectedClearAllRefinements />` to ignore that was my query.\r\n",
